{"word":"αἰκίζω","slug":"αἰκίζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>αἰκίζω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>attic for epic <el>αεἰκίζω</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>Act.</a></a> only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a>, <i>to treat injuriously, to plague, torment</i>, <el>τινά</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; of a storm, <el>αἰκίζων φόβην ὕλης</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be tormented</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a> in same sense as <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>Act.</a></a>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> dupl. <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> et rei, <el>αἰκίζεσθαί τινα τὰ ἔσχατα</el> <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}